A number with no fractional part, including the negative and positive numbers as well as zero.
A unit of cell concentration expressed as a number of cells per unit volume equal to one microliter.
A Circulatory Process consists of functions of cellular, cell, or tissue components of the heart and vessels by which blood and lymph is circulated through the body.
